    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-07-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="225"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 441.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">London,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-07-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 1, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I transmit, out of the ordinary course, a report
                    of the proceedings in the House of Commons last night, on the motion made by Mr.
                    Roebuck. It is difficult to imagine a more awkward situation than that in which
                    he has succeeded in placing as well his own government as the Emperor of the
                    French.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES FRANCIS ADAMS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
